<section id="why" class="why section-pad section-gap" aria-labelledby="why-title">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <div class="eyebrow">I · The problem</div>
    <h2 id="why-title" class="why-h2">
      LLMs forget. Agents reinvent the wheel every session.
      Teams of agents can't share what they learn.
    </h2>

    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-col">
        <div class="eyebrow col-label">What's missing today</div>
        <ul class="problem-list" role="list">
          <li><strong>SaaS lock-in</strong> — your memory hosted on someone else's server</li>
          <li><strong>Heavy stacks</strong> — Postgres + pgvector + Neo4j just to remember things</li>
          <li><strong>Built for humans</strong>, not agents — no ACL, no multi-tenancy, no MCP</li>
          <li><strong>Transient context</strong>, not persistent KB — forgets between sessions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="why-col">
        <div class="eyebrow col-label">What Gradatum does</div>
        <p class="why-answer">
          One Rust binary. SQLite + Markdown on disk.
          No PostgreSQL. No Redis. No SaaS.
          Pluggable LLM (or none). Multi-vault. Hierarchical ACL.
          Hybrid search — BM25 (SQLite FTS5) + semantic (cosine) + PageRank.
          The Markdown files are the source of truth — not the index.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .why {
    background: var(--paper);
  }

  .why-inner {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .why-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.875rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    max-width: 56rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .why-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
  }

  .col-label {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  }

  .problem-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.875rem;
  }

  .problem-list li {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
  }

  .problem-list li::before {
    content: '— ';
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .why-answer {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .why-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
